content: I am glad to see so many of you here today!
The fact that I would teach today came to me as a surprise 20 minutes ago.
but nevertheless, i am sure we will have a joyful lesson
to me, as a surprise 1 minute ago.
Today, I will select some interesting games from latest world championship, which have some theoretical or analytical interest.
And we will together discuss them,
finiding the ideas and solutions all together.
But before we begin, lets get our fingers warmed up.

skywalker, Yue, oddgod, slappanu, attila, dongfujia, lq20008, JumpingJack, Samsone, slamduk, shuwang, lkogr, tommy, xinxin, xuwu, blueice, ice, ying666666, Whiz, stiga, Ikon, yaya, sosei, ouyang, weigui.
It is very interesting in the theoretical aspect
This is a known theory so far
but the conclusions are sometimes varying from one side to another
may notice that the first 14 moves are exactly the same as from game Chingin-Meritee
I mean, I was black there
And Chingin surprised me with this 14th move in 2003
However, I was able to win the game as black, quite confidently.
what do you think about it?
many 15 to choose from,, hard to say which is the best
It seems to me, black is playing too straight on the left,
by such way, he does not utilize the sources of 3_9, and 13_11
but do you think the left side alone is sufficient for black win?
black mayebe risk,if not he have sufficient confidence.
not really, white still have some open lines
I guess white can defend in many ways here
who wants to be white now
it turns out to be a struggle in the positional style game
it seems white did not get the easy advantage
Lets see how sushkov decided to defend here
its a key connecting point actually,
every time when black takes it,
black will have good connections with all the areas
and also its a good defense point for black
Now , white took it! so lets see what comes from this.
Its obvious that if black plays passively to j7 now,
then white will take the total control
therefore Andersson has no choice, but to continue the attack plan
he used a four, before playing g7
but we, as analysers, lets check the g7 without four first
what would you do as white now? if anyone has an idea, say mr
so now we learned that black should take g8 point first
And now, black has been surrounded by whites
it means, its too late to switch to positional style,
so Andersson had to keep attacking straight
And now, the situation is so hopeless, that white could easily block the black win with any move.
can this move defend? yes or no
And now, let us recall the tactics of renju,
the best defense is not always the best move
do you know what it means?
lets say, before playing the next move, blacks potential equals to 100
by playing the white stone, we reduce black potential
this move maybe reduces black power from 100 to 40
because now, black has still much power left
22-f7 is the best defense! because it reduces opponents power most
do you understand me so far?
even though 22-h5 and e5 are worse defense moves,
they are also sufficient enough to defend against win.
And the "best move" is chosen from these choices, which "do not lose"
and the evaluation is - which move gives most benefit for white attack.
since f7, e5 and h5 all can survive,
so we dont need to care which one is "best defense",
because they all can survive well
so we choose from the aspect of white's own benefit
So, f7 is a best defense, but h5 is overall best move
If you learn to think that way in renju every time,
We should consider the white's power when defense.
your level will improve a lot
thats how 8 dan player is different from 4 dan player
4 dan player would have choses f7 as the "best defense"
but sometimes dare not choose the best move.
its the blindness of a master
Can we name it "best attaking defence"?
of course, easy vcf do you see?
he was so "far ahead" in his thinking,
so he missed the simplest threat
in fact, white has a chance to defend here
do you remember, what i told you some minutes ago about "best defense" and "best move"
in renju, you need to play "best moves" only!
i think many moves can defend here
whereas h12 is certainly the best one
because its sufficient enough for defense,
and same time helps white win
one must to be hi dan player to use this rule
now, black does not have vct anymore
are you afraid that black goes to f9 himself?
remember the rule of using four:
when do we use a four?
when we need four than we use it
then you can make a right decision every time
3. when we fear that opponent would take that point and the result is better for opponent after that
and it was not the forced defense
because white had other defenses too
it does not give black any benefit
white does NOT need to use the four
because it can always use it Anytime Later
since black will not go f9 now
black have vcf immediately, maybe D4
therefore, white has to take care of this threat,
and at the same time keep its own VCF threat
does white have vcf threat now?
Actually we saw that black's attack was really hopeless
and the left side is not strong enough to win alone without other areas support
I believe this move is much better!
and where would you play next black move?
but i still feel, without the support of 13_11, black cannot win
after that, everything went smoothly for black

this is how their game went on

But after the game he told us, he had sure win!
who wants to try black stones here
but hopefully we will find out soon
i just think after 26 black has win
so Andry was this close to victory!
So, it was very dramatic game

We have 5 minutes left, and I will show you one more example,
Who has seen this 11th move before?
this 15th move is a big question mark
From the 27th move, the straight theory ends, and the positional game begins,
whereas its not very clear what white should do here
the game was played between Andersson and Karlsson
White tried to gain advantage on left side,
because its the only hopeful area for white
but Andersson was calm and played well as black
I didnt SEE that 34_28 line was open
even the top players sometimes get blinded
Imagine, if he had just played here,
then, black would get the good positional advantage everywhere
and it would be amazing to think, that the variant begun with such crazy 11th move.
So, you all have something to analyse at home now
see if you can find better plan for white,
Because people always say, this 11th is a loss
so I want to know where
Thank you all for joining this lesson! I Wish you a pleasant evening and may you win more games in future! :)
